President Joe Biden has announced his nominees for key positions in his administration. The nominees include Elizabeth Allen for Under Secretary for Public Diplomacy at the Department of State, Joshua Jacobs for Under Secretary for Benefits at the Department of Veterans Affairs, Ron Borzekowski for Director of the Office of Financial Research at the Department of Treasury, David J. Kostelancik for Ambassador to the Republic of Albania, Cynthia Kierscht for Ambassador to the Republic of Djibouti, Jennifer L. Johnson for Ambassador to the Federated States of Micronesia, Julie Turner for Special Envoy on North Korean Human Rights Issues, Liliana Ayalde for Member of the Inter-American Foundation, Marcela Escobari for Member of the Inter-American Foundation, Maria Fabiana Jorge for Member of the Inter-American Foundation, Brian Nichols for Member of the Inter-American Foundation, Julio Guity-Guevara for Member of the Inter-American Foundation, Carol Moseley Braun for Chair of the United States African Development Foundation, Monde Muyangwa for Member of the United States African Development Foundation, Kathryn Lang for Member of the Social Security Advisory Board.